test_exception_lower_ir
=======================

IR-structure regression tests for the `saw-tools/exception-lower` pass,
complementing the SAW-level behavioural test in `test_exception_lower/`.

The behavioural test pins down what the *output* of the pass should mean;
this test pins down properties of the *transformation itself*: which
constructs must disappear, which must remain, and that the output passes
LLVM's IR verifier.

Coverage
--------

* `phi_before_landingpad.ll` — two `invoke`s share an unwind block that
  begins with a PHI node above its `landingpad`.  The PHI must survive
  (with predecessor labels updated to the new `.ehcheck` blocks) and
  the landingpad must still be lowered.  This is the case that the
  original pass missed because it inspected only the front instruction
  of the unwind block.
* `throw_then_unreachable.ll` — a bare `__cxa_throw` followed by
  `unreachable`.  The trailing dead code must be erased after the
  synthesized `ret`.
* `rethrow.ll` — `__cxa_rethrow` from inside a (notional) catch frame.
  The flag must be re-set and the trailing `unreachable` must be erased.

Running
-------

The test runs automatically as part of `cabal test integration-tests`,
but exits 0 ("skipped") when the `exception-lower` binary or LLVM
`opt` / `llvm-dis` cannot be found.  To force the test to run with a
specific build of the pass:

    EXCEPTION_LOWER=/path/to/exception-lower bash test.sh
